The paper may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with generating new views of a scene, which is a common problem in computer graphics. 

The paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes an end-to-end model for the task of single image view synthesis, which is a common approach in machine learning research. 

The paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it proposes a model that can generate new views of a scene without any ground-truth 3D information, which is a challenging problem in artificial intelligence research. 

Finally, the paper may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it proposes a model that allows for interpretable manipulation of the latent feature space at test time, which is a common problem in robotics research.
